Tool Used: I used Canva to create the infographic. It’s a user-friendly design platform that allowed me to combine text, icons, and colors in an organized way.

Topic Coverage: The infographic effectively covers the main topics of my project, including cybercrime types, online safety tips, UPI/financial security, and reporting channels. It presents the information in a concise and structured format that is both informative and engaging.

Reflection: Creating this infographic taught me how to present complex information visually. I realized that good design can make content more understandable and memorable. Choosing layouts, colors, and icons was initially challenging, but experimenting in Canva made the process enjoyable and helped me improve my visual communication skills.
